fix:
public T[] sample(int sampleSize) throws NotStrictlyPositiveException {
    if (sampleSize <= 0) {
        throw new NotStrictlyPositiveException(LocalizedFormats.NUMBER_OF_SAMPLES,
                sampleSize);
    }

    List<T> tempSingletonCache = Lists.newArrayList();

    Class<? extends T> cacheType = null;
    for (final Triplet<String, String, Object> triplet : distribution) {
      try {
        final double value = ((Number) triplet.getValue()).doubleValue();
        if (value > 0) {
          int times = (int) Math.floor(value * sampleSize); 

          // get the class of objects in singletons and store it into cacheType variable
          if (cacheType == null){
            cacheType = (Class<? extends T>) triplet.getFirst().getClass();
          }

          // fill up temporary singleton cache with objects according to their frequency
          IntStream.rangeClosed(0, times).forEach(idx -> {
            tempSingletonCache.add((T)triplet.getFirst());
          });
        }

      } catch (final ArithmeticException e) {
        // Value too large, downscale
        long tmpVal = Math.round(value * sampleSize);
        IntStream.rangeClosed(0, (int)tmpVal).forEach(idx -> {
          tempSingletonCache.add((T)triplet.getFirst());
        });
      }

    }

    final RandomDataGenerator randGen = new RandomDataGenerator();
    while (tempSingletonCache.size() < sampleSize) {
      tempSingletonCache.add(randGen.nextUniform(0, 1) < 0.5 ?
              randomSingleton() : singleton());
    }

    Collections.shuffle(tempSingletonCache, random);

    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
    final T[] out = (T[]) java.lang.reflect.Array.newInstance(cacheType , sampleSize);

    // fill up output array from temporary singleton cache
    IntStream.range(0, sampleSize).forEach(idx -> {
      out[idx] = tempSingletonCache.get(idx);
    });

    return out;

}

issue_description:
Creating an array with Array.newInstance(singletons.get(0).getClass(), sampleSize) in DiscreteDistribution.sample(int) is risky. An exception will be thrown if:

singleons.get(0) is of type T1, an sub-class of T, and
DiscreteDistribution.sample() returns an object which is of type T, but not of type T1.

To reproduce:

List<Pair<Object,Double>> list = new ArrayList<Pair<Object, Double>>();
list.add(new Pair<Object, Double>(new Object() {}, new Double(0)));
list.add(new Pair<Object, Double>(new Object() {}, new Double(1)));
new DiscreteDistribution<Object>(list).sample(1);

Attaching a patch.

